# IoT Project Rubric Filling Guide
## Review Goal

The goal is to identify projects that are open enough, understandable enough, and relevant enough to adopt, adapt, update, or improve for small and mid-sized farms through adoption, adaptation, training, and stewardship.

## Purpose

The rubric is designed to help reviewers sort projects by category and subcategory, then compare them across practical criteria such as activity, documentation, usability, farm relevance, and openness. The spreadsheet structure aligns well with common agriculture-IoT, smart-farming, precision-agriculture, and organic-agriculture topic groupings found on GitHub, which makes it easier to collect comparable projects in one place.
It standardizes how to classify projects, score them consistently, and record practical notes that support later sorting, field-testing, and stewardship decisions.




